                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Golf &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Confederation Park Golf Course is a public golf course offering an advanced nine-hole course, a putting green, and a two-level hitting bay. The course provides a challenging yet fantastic mix of par-three, four, and five holes. Plus, golfers have easy access to the driving range. There is a small but well-stocked clubhouse attached to the golf course, which is well-maintained by friendly and well-trained staff. The golf course also offers a Pace of Play improvement program for those ready to speed up their game. </p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Banff Trail is dotted with parks connected by the North Hill recreational pathway system that runs through these parks right up to Nose Creek. Younger children love the small local playgrounds designed to give their growing bodies the exercise they need. One such playground is <strong>Cathedral Road NW Playground</strong>, well-equipped with modern and safe playground equipment for younger children and a ball diamond. Major parks in the area include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Canmore Park (also known as North Capitol Hill Park) </strong> has something to offer the entire family. The park has a playground, pool, tennis courts, ball diamonds, a trail, picnic facilities, a spray park, splash pad, and even facilities for snowboarding and skiing.</p>
                        <li><strong>Banff Trail Park on 20th Avenue NW</strong> is another park enjoyed by Banff Trail’s residents. It has a playground for toddlers, a ball diamond for older children, and a community garden for parents who enjoy gardening.</p>
                        <li><strong>Foothills Athletic Park</strong> is a sports hub in northwest Calgary and a favourite for those who enjoy tennis, soccer, Frisbee, and little league baseball. The facility has a massive indoor ice arena, swimming pool, and soccer pitches.</p>
                        <li><strong>Confederation Park</strong> is a 160-hectare urban park comprising a wooded area with paths for hikers and bikers. The is a popular desitnation in the winter for cross-county skiing. Playgrounds, benches, tunnels, little bridges, a wetland for bird viewing, and a duck pond are just some family attractions in this picturesque location. The urban park is also pooch-friendly, so don’t hesitate to bring your furry friend along.</p>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
