        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>The City of Calgary Census of 2016 reported that 3,760 residents stayed in 1,595 private households that year. There is a large population of children in the area. About 84% of the population comprises Canadian citizens, and the rest are not Canadian citizens. More than 77% of the population’s mother tongue is English.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>More than 50% of Banff Trail’s dwellings were built before 1960. Many of these have been renovated to appeal to younger families looking for modern lifestyles. With a new redevelopment plan, potential owners can expect to find new constructions in the retail market. Houses here consist of single-family homes and condominiums offering a wide and eclectic range of living options for different lifestyles – all visually appealing and charming.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Developer/builder/history</h3>
            <p>Banff Trail is named after the town Banff. Banff Trail became a part of Calgary when it was annexed to the city in 1910. The land on which this lush green neighbourhood stands proudly today was a once barren land with no trees and little brush. Today, it is teeming with trees, parks, and green spaces and is one of Calgary's most sought-after neighbourhoods.</p>
        </div>
