    <div style="margin-top: 80px;">
        <h2>FAQs about Banff Trail Real Estate and Neighborhood</h2>
        <ol>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Will I feel safe in this neighbourhood?</h3>
                <p>Most crime here is petty and related to vandalism. Residents have peace of mind that the nearest police facility is only 2 km away, on 14th Street SW. The nearest fire station is even closer, on 16th Avenue NW.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>How will I get around the area?</h3>
                <p>Banff Trail is a walkable neighbourhood, but it is car-dependant and will require driving around to complete most errands. The community is close to the Banff Trail station – a CTrain Light rail station that gets residents to other parts of Calgary. There is reliable public transit and several ride-sharing and taxi companies serving the area. At least two bus lines pass through the community. The neighbourhood has some biking infrastructure.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Is there a pool nearby?</h3>
                <p>The Foothills Aquatic Centre on Union Hills Drive is a multi-purpose recreation facility offering many programs and facilities. The centre has an indoor six-lane 25-meter pool, a dive tank, and a safe kiddie wading pool. The centre also provides drop-in swim and fitness classes and swimming lessons.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Will the kids have access to extracurricular activities?</h3>
                <p>Yes. Banff Trail is a child-friendly neighbourhood that provides children ample opportunities to take some time away from their studies and learn something new. The community association hosts a wide variety of programs for children. There are several recreational facilities in and around the neighbourhood, like the Foothills Athletic Park.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>How long will it take to get to the airport?</h3>
                <p>Calgary international airport is less than a 20-minute from Banff Trail, and the AB-2 N route is a little less than 17 km away. The Trans-Canada Highway/AB-1 E and AB-2 N route places the airport about 18.3 km away. The shortest distance to the airport is via 14 Street NW, but it’s not always the fastest route because of traffic.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div><!-- Banff Trail FAQs -->

